# FF Orbit MCP Architecture

Orbit is snapshot-first.
- Snapshot: local point-in-time project files.
- Index: symbols/edges extracted from snapshot.
- Changeset: draft edits + preview + validation + apply.

Core tool signature:
```ts
orbit({ cmd: string, args?: object, snapshot?: string, format?: "json"|"explain" })
```

Primary command groups:
- Discovery: `projects.list`, `snapshots.create`, `snapshots.refresh`, `snapshots.refreshSlow`, `snapshots.ensureFresh`, `snapshots.info`, `snapshots.ls`
- Query: `pages.list`, `page.get`, `widgets.list`, `textfields.list`, `widget.get`, `widget.getMany`, `widgets.find`, `search`
- Edit: `page.create`, `page.update`, `page.remove`, `page.clone`, `widget.create`, `widget.set`, `widget.delete`, `routes.upsert`, `routes.delete`
- Safety: `changeset.preview`, `changeset.validate`, `changeset.apply`, `changeset.applySafe`, `changeset.rollback`, `changeset.drop`

Prefer deterministic commands over exploratory probing.

Current reliability features:
- `snapshots.refresh` supports `fetchStrategy: auto|bulk|file`.
- `snapshots.refresh` supports chunked full file mode (`chunkedFull`) to avoid relisting each pass.
- `changeset.applySafe` supports bounded 429 retry controls.
- `intent.run` can map natural refresh prompts to `snapshots.refresh`.
